    "causal_summary": "Packet 015 showed `llama-cpp` is much faster than `hf-local`, but vector-to-vector parity failed with mean cosine `0.9677582325103543` against a `0.995` target. That parity test compared corresponding vectors, not retrieval behavior. The open question is whether the cosine miss changes actual search ranking enough to block a future default flip.",
